      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match VAD operating envelope including blood analog fluid properties, rotational speed range, and pressure head at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used a glycerin-water blood analog rather than porcine blood. Viscosity and yield stress deviations introduce systematic differences in shear-induced hemolysis. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
